Guidelines on Applications for a Youth Mobility Scheme (YMS) Resident Visa to the Republic of China (Taiwan) by Citizens of the United Kingdom

    Qualification of Applicants
    Applicants for a YMS resident visa to the Republic of China (Taiwan) should possess the following qualifications:
        be UK citizens residing in the UK at the time of application;
        have never before obtained a YMS resident visa to the Republic of China (Taiwan);
        be between 18 and 30 years in age, inclusively;
        not planning to be accompanied by dependents during the time in Taiwan; and
        have submitted all required documents.
    To apply for a YMS resident visa, applicants should submit the following documents:
        completed application form for YM resident visa (signed personally) and application form for the YMS Approval Letter;
        a resume;
        a passport valid for a minimum of 1 year at the time of submission;
        two 2”x 2” color photographs taken within six months prior to application;
        proof of travel medical insurance coverage during one’s stay in the Republic of China (Taiwan), which should be valid for at least the first 4 months of the planned stay;
        round-trip flight ticket or proof of sufficient funds for the purchase of a return trip;
        proof of sufficient financial means, such as traveler’s checks or bank statements to the value of ￡1600;
        the equivalent of US$66 in British pounds for the application fee.
    Application Procedures
        Applications may be made in person, by an authorised third party or by post.
        Applications must be submitted to the London Office or to the Edinburgh Office of the Taipei Representative Office in the UK.
        Applicants may be requested to provide additional documents or to be interviewed as necessary.
    Type of Visa Issued
        Type: Resident Visa 
        Duration of stay: 1 year, starting from the day after the date of entry
        Application for Alien Resident Certificates (ARC) and restrictions: Those entering Taiwan on a YMS resident visa must apply for an ARC and a Re-entry Permit at local service centers of the National Immigration Agency within 15 days starting from the day after the date of entry. Once this step is completed, they will not be allowed to change their visa status while in Taiwan.
